Korean daily apologizes for A-bomb editorial
2013-05-27 08:59:20 GMT
By Zhang Yujie, Sina EnglishSouth Korea’s JoongAng Ilbo on Monday issued an apology about an editorial saying the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki were “divine punishment,” which sparked strong protest in Japan.The paper stated that the editorial violated the ethics of the paper, and they sincerely apologize to the bomb victims and their relatives for causing so much trauma and pain.Last week, an editorial in the daily’s Korean and English versions said the 1945 nuclear bombs dropped by U.S. planes, which together killed more than 200,000 people, were justified. 
